      "body": "Similarly, in Weex like this:\n\n``` javascript\n<div repeat=\"{{(i, v) in array}}\" class=\"{{i === array.length - 1 ? 'last-child' : ''}}\"></div>\n```\n\nBut, if you don't like this special style, you also can do this as a sugar:\n\n``` javascript\n<template>\n  <div>\n    <div repeat=\"{{(i, v) in list}}\" class=\"{{lastChild(i)}}\">\n      <text>{{v}}</text>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</template>\n\n<style>\n  .lastChild {\n    color: red;\n  }\n</style>\n\n<script>\n  module.exports = {\n    data: {\n      list: [1, 2]\n    },\n    methods: {\n      lastChild: function(i) {\n        if (i === this.list.length - 1) {\n          return 'lastChild'\n        }\n        return ''\n      }\n    }\n  }\n</script>\n```\n"
    }
  ],
  "created_at": "2016-05-17T11:36:43Z",
